question:
Find the real values of $m$ for which the following set of vectors $V=\left( \begin{array}{r}  
1\\ 
2 \\
m \end{array}
\right)$, $Z=\left( \begin{array}{r}  
1\\ 
-1 \\
m \end{array}
\right)$, and
$W=\left( \begin{array}{r}  
3\\ 
m+2 \\
1 \end{array}
\right)$ is linearly independent.

Indicate which of the following is a linear combination of $A=\left[\begin{array}{rr}
      3& 2\\
			0 & 1 
    \end{array}\right]$, $B=\left[\begin{array}{rr}
      0& -1 \\
			1 & 2 
    \end{array}\right]$ and $C=\left[\begin{array}{rr}
      5& 4 \\
			-1 & 0
    \end{array}\right]$.

Let  $A=\left( \begin{array}{rrr}
1 & 2 & 0\\ 
1 & 0 & 2\\ 
0 & 1 & 1\end{array}
\right)$ and $g\left(x\right)=x^2-2x-3I_{3\times 3}$. Find $\mathrm{det} \left(g(A) \right)$.
